<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="931" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d931">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15314.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Confidential Agent of the
                                    Provisional Government of Mexico</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Pursuant to instructions just
                            received from General Villa, I have the honor to inform your excellency
                            that General Roque Gonzalez Garza, having resigned as President of the
                            Sovereign Convention charged with the federal Executive Power, Mr.
                            Francisco Lagos Cházaro, has been designated by the Convention as his
                            successor.</p>
                        <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Enrique C. Llorente.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>